participate\n111\n\n_lUt_,,\n\n1.1,\n\nUlll\n\nv_,|\n\nin\nol_l_o\n\nare considered\nas partners\nwith government\nand industry in the nation\'s aerospace program.\nNASA\'s\nobjective is to have them bring their scientific, engineering,\nand social research\ncompetence\nto bear\non aerospace\nproblems\nand on the broader\nsocial, economic,\nand international\ni/nplications\nof\nNASA\'s technical and scientific programs.\nIt is expected that, in so doing, universities will strengthen\nboth their research\nand their educational\ncapabilities\nto contribute\nmore effectively\nto the national\nwell-being.\n\nNASA\nField Centers\nand certain\nHeadquarters\nProgram\nOffices provide\nfunds for those\nR&D\nactivities\nin universities\nwhich contribute\nto the mission\nneeds of that particular\nNASA element.\nAlthough\nNASA\nhas no predetermined\namount\nof money to devote\nto university\nactivities,\nthe\neffort funded\neach year is substantial.\n(See the bar chart on the next page).\nThis annual report is\none means of documenting\nthe NASA-university\nrelationship,\nfrequently\ndenoted,\ncollectively,\nas\nNASA\'s\nUniversity\nProgram.\n\nThe Office of University\nAffairs\n(OUA)\nserves as a focal point for NASA\'s\nrelationships\nwith\ncolleges and universities.\nOne of its roles is to provide\ninformation\non the NASA\nUniversity\nProgram.\nThe present document\nis designed\nto serve several purposes\nand a wide range of audiences\nfrom private\nindividuals\nto NASA\nemployees.\nThe emphasis\nis on the technical\ncontent\nof the\nprogram,\nrather than on fiscal data, which is available separately\nfrom OUA.\nAs some terminology\nwill not be familiar\nto all readers,\na "User\'s\nGuide"\nis included\nto facilitate\nthe Fhe accession\nnumber has meaning only in this report; it is in no way permanently\nassociated\nwith nor does it uniquely\nidentify\na specific grant or contract\nanywhere\nexcept in the present report.\nAccession\nnumbers\nare assigned\nsequentially\nto the citations,\nbeginning\nwith 1000.\nThus, when an\nentry of interest\nis identified\nin any one of the Appendices,\nthe\nready location\nof the full description\nin the body of the report.\n\nassociated\n\naccession\n\nnumber\n\nAppendix\n\nA -\n\nGiven only the grant or contract\nnumber\nthis index enables the reader\nto
